Proposed new structure for merb.thor:

1) use Merb module instead of Merb class (no more < Thor)
2) extract source handling (git related tasks) into SourceManagement module
3) keep merb:gems and merb:source 'raw' tasks (but use the new Thor grouping: thor -T --all OR --group developer)
4) use merb:depencies for application bundle tasks (alternatively merb:application)
5) use merb:system for system-wide tasks (alternatively merb:stack)
6) use merb:tasks for utility tasks (merb:tasks:update etc. - setup will be implicit now)
7) use dm: namespace for specific dm tasks (merb:stack could delegate to this?)
8) use sequel: or active_record: namespaces in a similar fashion
(no more polution of merb namespace with 3rd party ORM etc.)

Merb::Dependencies (alternatively: Merb::Application)
- merb:dependencies:list (show application dependencies - will show local vs. system gems)
- merb:dependencies:config (write config/dependencies.yml)
- merb:dependencies:bundle (bundle dependencies with the app - aliased to :install):

merb:dependencies:bundle [STRATEGY] (currently: stable and edge)
method_options "--merb-root"    => :optional, # operate on this directory
               "--version"      => :optional, # specify a version for framework components
               "--sources"      => :optional, # specify a sources.yml for git/edge sources
               "--all"          => :boolean,  # install all sub-dependencies of the gems
               "--framework"    => :boolean,  # only install framework components
               "--config"       => :boolean,  # use config/dependencies.yml
               "--config-file"  => :optional  # use the specified dependencies.yml

Merb::System (alternatively: Merb::Stack)
- merb:system:list (show currently installed framework components)
- merb:system:install (install framework components system-wide):

merb:system:install [STRATEGY] (currently: stable and edge)
method_options "--merb-root"    => :optional, # operate on this directory
               "--version"      => :optional, # specify a version for framework components
               "--sources"      => :optional, # specify a sources.yml for git/edge sources
               "--all"          => :boolean,  # install all sub-dependencies of the gems
               "--framework"    => :boolean,  # only install framework components
               "--config"       => :boolean,  # use config/dependencies.yml (user created)
               "--config-file"  => :optional  # use the specified dependencies.yml